    </ul>

    <h2>Multiple Results</h2>
    <p>
        You can request the RandomStuff API to return collections instead of single objects.
        The number of objects returned by the API is determined by the <b>size</b> parameter (default is 10).
    </p>
    <pre>{{ app.url_generator.generate('users_collection', {}, true) }}<span>?size=5</span></pre>

    <h2>Overriding values</h2>
    <p>
        RandomStuff gives you a couple ways to control the results that the
        system outputs. You can request specific values by giving them as GET
        parameter.
    </p>
    <pre style="margin-bottom: 50px;">{{ app.url_generator.generate('users_single', {}, true) }}<span>?birthday=1991-06-21&amp;name:first=Lily</span></pre>

    <h2>Seeds</h2>
    <p>
        In order to speed up your application, RandomStuff also allows you to
        always request the same information each time from the service. This is
        for both consistency, and it allows your browser to cache profile
        photos to speed up your loading time. RandomStuff accepts a "<b>seed</b>"
        parameter that will always return the same results.
    </p>
    <pre>{{ app.url_generator.generate('users_single', {}, true) }}<span>?seed=42</span></pre>

    <p>(note that giving a seed disable the values overriding feature)</p>

